text: Just ventingI have no idea who I am or what I am  This existence is like an incredibly intense and consistent fever dream  It started as a teenager  and I thought it d eventually stop  But it hasn t Suicide can be a beautiful thing  I understand why people feel the opposite  In one sense  it s absolutely horrible  Ending life  throwing oneself into the darkness forever and leaving behind anyone and everyone behind for complete silence  But this life is hard to navigate  and actually living it is like playing a game of chess where the pieces tower impossibly above you and the chessboard itself is a rough sea that s infinitely deep  There s immense beauty to be found under the water but it s all too easy to drown  and to move ahead in life you can t live under the water at all  You must continue gasping for air at the surface and must keep trying to push the chess pieces that are so big they touch the sky   I wish we lived in a world more empathetic to those who wanted to end their lives  I wish those who actually did have no one but wanted to live could replace those who have people but don t want to live  I know that sounds absolutely nightmarish but it s a nice idea in my crazy head   Mrs  Smith  your son was a miserable bastard as you know and so he s been replaced  Here s Derek  Derek s very nice and understands the world enough to want to be here  Forget about your old son  He s gone now  Your son is Derek As I ve grown older I ve become more and more truly inhibited and silent in my soul to be a civil human being  Deep down inside if I acted how I felt I d spin so madly I d tear everything down  I just keep it inside  I keep it inside
summary: Mrs Smith's son, Derek, has died and she's replaced him with a nice new son, who is nice and understands the world enough to want to be here. As he's grown older he's become more and more inhibited and silent.
